Manuscript Title: Outsized roles of elders within wildlife populations; age-related 
increases in salmon consumption by grizzlies and its ecological implications


Script Descriptions:

01_SalmonBiomassDensity.R:  calculates annual salmon biomass density per merged 
watershed (2008-2019); reproduces methods describe in section '2.31 – Salmon Biomass Density'
in the manuscript

02_SalmonDiversity_by_watershed.R: calculates annual Shannon diversity of salmon 
species per merged watershed (2008–2019); reproduces methods described in 
section '2.32 Salmon diversity' in the manuscript

03_EVI_by_Watershed.R: extracts mean spring–summer EVI from MODIS imagery per 
merged watershed (2008–2018); reproduces methods described in section 
'2.33 – Terrestrial plant productivity (vegetation) ' in the manuscript

04_attribute_covariotes.R: spatially joins bear locations to watersheds and 
attributes all covariates with a one-year lag; reproduces methods described in 
section '2.3 Covariate attribution' in the manuscript

05_glmm_analysis.R: fits and compares beta regression GLMMs; reproduces analyses 
described in section '2.4 Data Analysis' and results in section '3' in 
the manuscript

06_salmon_by_age.R: estimates absolute salmon consumption (kg) as bears age
using m1 model predictions and Kingsley (1983) growth curves; reproduces 
analyses described in section '2.41 – Estimating increase in salmon biomass 
consumption with age' in the manuscript

Data:
the following processed file is provided to complete all script 05 and 06:

all_cov_scaled_no_locations.csv: Final modelling dataset (550 individual-year 
combinations) with scaled covariates. UTM coordinates removed.



Code/Software
Analyses were conducted in R. R Core Team (2026). R: A language and environment 
for statistical computing. R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna,
Austria. URL https://www.R-project.org/. Version 2026.01.1+403 
